Parent/Guardian Signature: ________________________________________________________________

Club Mission Statement: The Falcon Basketball Club is more than a program — it’s a family. We believe basketball is a powerful tool for building character, confidence, and community. Our mission is to create a safe and encouraging environment where every young athlete can grow in skill, strength, and spirit. Through teaching the fundamentals of the game, we develop not only better players, but better teammates and future leaders. Together, we aim to inspire a lifelong love for basketball and a deep sense of pride in being part of the Falcon family.
Program: Young Athletes will be given the opportunity through the months of November, December, and February (In-Season) to participate in basketball skill sessions. Athletes can attend as many or as little sessions as they choose. The sessions will be breaking down into groups by grade:
Elementary Gym:
 K-1st
2nd-3rd 
Rec Center gym:
4th-5th-6th 
7th and 8th
By being part of the Falcon Basketball club, each athlete will be eligible to be chosen for Kid Captain. Kid Captains will receive 3 free passes paid for by the club to Varsity Home contest, a free Kid Captain Falcon Basketball T-Shirt, Photo with the team and signed memorabilia from high school athletes. Kid Captains will be introduced along with the team - be allowed to run out on the court with the team and sit with the team on the bench during the game. 
